This file defines the main layout for the dashboard section of the application. It arranges the application by placing a `Sidebar` on the left and the main content area to its right.

## Purpose

To provide a consistent structural foundation for all pages within the `/dashboard` route. This includes a persistent navigation sidebar and a scrollable main content area.

## Key Components

- **`Sidebar`**: Imported from `@/components/ui/sidebar`. This component renders the navigation sidebar.

## Props

- **`children`**: `React.ReactNode` - The content that will be rendered within the main area of the dashboard, typically other page components.

## Usage

This layout component is used in the `app/dashboard/layout.tsx` file itself. Any page or nested layout within the `/dashboard` route will automatically inherit this structure.

```tsx
// app/dashboard/layout.tsx
import { Sidebar } from "@/components/ui/sidebar";

export default function DashboardLayout({
  children,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode;
}) {
  return (
    <div className="flex h-screen bg-background overflow-hidden">
      <Sidebar />
      <main className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto">{children}</main>
    </div>
  );
}
```
